Builder.io AI Project Rules
Code Standards
Use TypeScript for all new components
Follow functional components with hooks pattern
Use CSS modules or Tailwind utilities only
No inline styles unless absolutely necessary
Implement proper error boundaries
Font System
Headings: 32px, 24px, 20px, 18px, 16px, 14px
Body: 16px (base), 14px (small), 12px (caption)
Use CSS custom properties: --font-size-xl, --font-size-lg, etc.
Responsive: reduce 10-20% on mobile breakpoints
Semantic classes: .text-xl, .text-lg, .text-base, .text-sm, .text-xs
Component Architecture
One component per file
Props interface at top of file
Default props when needed
Proper prop validation
Export component as default
File Organization
/components - Reusable UI components
/pages - Page-level components
/styles - Global styles and variables
/utils - Helper functions
/types - TypeScript type definitions
Performance Rules
Lazy load non-critical components
Optimize images (WebP, proper sizing)
Use React.memo for expensive renders
Avoid unnecessary re-renders
Always Apply These When Making Changes:
Maintain consistent font scaling
Use semantic HTML elements
Ensure accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)
Test responsive behavior
Follow existing naming conventions
Update related documentation
Never Do:
Use arbitrary font sizes outside the defined scale
Create duplicate utility classes
Skip TypeScript types
Use any type
Ignore console warnings/errors